{"id":7988,"date":"2017-11-01T19:52:42","date_gmt":"2017-11-02T02:52:42","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/?p=7988"},"modified":"2024-01-07T13:11:33","modified_gmt":"2024-01-07T21:11:33","slug":"mount-grohman","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2017\/11\/01\/mount-grohman\/","title":{"rendered":"MOUNT GROHMAN"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong><em>MOUNT GROHMAN<\/em><\/strong>\u00a0 \u00a0 2295m\u00a0 \u00a07531&#8242;<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><em>Walking up Grohman Creek is a good early-season hike along a spectacular creek and waterfall.<br \/>\nMount Grohman is a lovely off-trail ridge-line hike. The access road takes you way up in the alpine. The route is surrounded by prominent peaks and landmarks. It is easy to get turned around on the ridges, especially on the hike back.<br \/>\n<\/em><em>Grohman Creek also gives a backdoor entrance to Pulpit Rock.<\/em><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Rating: \u2666\u2666\u2666\u2666\u25ca<br \/>\nDifficulty: <\/strong>C2 difficult<strong><br \/>\n<\/strong><strong>Distance:<\/strong>\u00a08kms round trip<br \/>\n<strong>Elevation gain:<\/strong> +617m<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"> <strong>Key elevations:<\/strong> Baldface Lodge 6700&#8242;, Summit 7531&#8242;<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"> <strong>Time:<\/strong> 7 hours round trip<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"> <strong>Season:<\/strong> June through October<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"> <strong>Access:<\/strong> Good<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"> <strong>Map:<\/strong> 82F\/11 Kokanee Creek<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Drive. <\/strong>Drive and park at Baldface Lodge, about a 1 hour up Grohman FSR. 2WD low-clearance vehicle<strong><br \/>\n<\/strong>From Nelson, turn on Marsden Road. <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">0.0 km. Immediately fork left. <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">8.2 km. Cross a bridge over Grohman Creek and turn left. <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">9.9 km. Cross Grohman Creek again.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">11 km, turn right at the sign for Baldface Lodge and ascend. <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">15.2 km. Fork left and follow the Baldface sign (right leads to the CBC Tower on Elephant Mountain) and switch back high. <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">21.7 km. Continue straight towards the lodge. <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">22 km. Park by Baldface Lodge, a 1000m elevation gain.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Route\/Trail. <\/strong>From behind Baldface Lodge, follow a faint summer trail up to the ridge. Mt Grohman is behind a small peak. Head north to the small peak that has a radio tower and naked-lady sculpture (the Kootenay Lady) at its top.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Descend the small peak, and walk the long ridge line north to Mt. Grohman. 2.5 hours to the summit.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong><em>Return<\/em><\/strong> the same way.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><strong>Reference:<\/strong> https:\/\/westkootenayhiking.ca\/?s=Mt+Grohman+<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>MOUNT GROHMAN\u00a0 \u00a0 2295m\u00a0 \u00a07531&#8242; Walking up Grohman Creek is a 